article.headline: Williams, UCF smother Memphis, advance to AAC tourney semis

images.name: Fall sends shot into the stands
images.caption: UCF big man Tacko Fall rejects Dedric Lawson's baseline jumper.

article.linkText: Williams, UCF smother Memphis, advance to AAC tourney semis
article.story:
HARTFORD, Conn. -- Matt Williams had 19 points, including five 3-pointers, B.J. Taylor scored 14 with five assists and No. 4 seed UCF beat fifth-seeded Memphis 84-54 on Friday in the American Athletic Conference Tournament.

UCF (21-10) will play top-seeded and No. 12-ranked SMU in the semifinals on Saturday. The Knights, who have won six in a row, lost their only regular-season meeting with SMU.

After a dunk by Rivers gave Memphis a 10-4 lead, the Tigers missed their next 14 field-goal attempts and went scoreless for more than 5 1/2 minutes as UCF scored 18 straight points to start a 33-7 run and take a 43-26 lead into halftime. The Knights hit six 3-pointers, including three in a row by Williams, during the stretch. UCF then opened the second half with an 11-1 run to open a 27-point lead and cruised from there.

Brothers Dedric and K.J. Lawson combined for 22 points, 12 rebounds and six assists for Memphis (19-13), but made just 7 of 24 shots. The Tigers, who have lost six of their last seven games, were held 20 points below their scoring average (74.6).

videos.headline: Lawson finds Rivers to put Memphis up by six points early
videos.description: Tigers guard K.J. Lawson finds a streaking Jimario Rivers for the one-handed slam.

videos.headline: Davis nails the 3-pointer for UCF
videos.description: A.J. Davis steps up and drains the three for UCF, part of a 18-0 run for the Knights.

videos.headline: Banyard nails the jumper for UCF, plus the foul
videos.description: UCF forward Nick Banyard increases the Knights' big lead as he drains the long two, plus the foul.

videos.headline: Fall gets the pass inside and finishes with the dunk
videos.description: UCF big man Tacko Fall slams it with ease to put the Knights up 56-29

videos.headline: Williams drains the long three for UCF
videos.description: Matt Williams sinks his fifth 3-pointer of the game as he gives the Knights a 22-point lead.

videos.headline: Taylor finds Fall for the alley-oop slam to increase UCF's lead
videos.description: B.J. Taylor lobs one up for Tacko Fall, who finishes easily with the slam.
